This paper deals with image-to-image translation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework utilizes new non-adversarial cycle losses, which suggests that it may fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions PET-CT translation and MR motion correction, indicating that it may be related to medical imaging (cs.MM). Finally, the use of unsupervised learning suggests that it may also be relevant to neural networks (cs.NE).
